title: Population in Sweden 2018 , by level of education
summary: This bar chart has 8 columns on the x axis representing Level Of Education, and Share of population in each Level Of Education on the y axis.
Level Of Education Upper secondary education (3 years or more) has the highest Share of population and Post-graduate education has the lowest Share of population.
There is a difference of 22.28 between the maximum Level Of Education Upper secondary education (3 years or more) and minimum Level Of Education Post-graduate education.
min_summary: This is a bar chart representing Level Of Education in the x axis and Share of population in the y axis.
Level Of Education Upper secondary education (3 years or more) has the highest Share of population and Post-graduate education has the lowest Share of population.
mid_summary: This bar chart has 8 columns on the x axis representing Level Of Education, and Share of population in each Level Of Education on the y axis.
Level Of Education Upper secondary education (3 years or more) has the highest Share of population and Post-graduate education has the lowest Share of population.

max_summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Share of population for 8 number of Level Of Educations.
Level Of Education Upper secondary education (3 years or more) has the highest Share of population and Post-graduate education has the lowest Share of population.
Level Of Education Post-secondary education (3 years or more) has the second highest value for Share of population.
The difference of Share of population between the highest and lowest Level Of Education is 22.28.

The Level Of Education Upper secondary education (3 years or more) has the highest Share of population, followed by Post-secondary education (3 years or more), and Upper secondary education (less than 3 years). Down to the Level Of Education Post-graduate education which is the lowest.
The Level Of Education Upper secondary education (3 years or more) has 1.87 times more Share of population than average.
The Share of population is 100.12 if we add up values of all Level Of Educations.
